# Backend API Boundaries

Apply this rule when editing backend route/controller/service/database code.

## Layering Expectations

- Keep route files thin: route registration only.
- Keep controller files focused on request parsing/response mapping.
- Keep business rules in service files.
- Keep DB schema/query concerns in DB/service layers.

## Contract Discipline

- If request/response behavior changes, update shared contracts in `shared/`.
- Keep API envelope semantics consistent.
- Add or update route tests for changed behavior.
